  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Disaster Risk Reduction for Kismayo IDP Sites at Risk of Flooding</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">This project aims at developing structural flood mitigation measures by establishing, rehabilitating and enhancing drainage systems in internally displaced persons (IDP) sites in Kismayo, Somalia, to increase the capacity of IDP communities to respond to future shocks and threats. IOM will also train community leaders, including women groups on camp coordination and camp management modalities, flood mitigation and response.</narrative>
  </description>
